# Notes detail (frozen)

Read **`docs/specs/NOTES_DETAIL_CONSTRAINTS.md`** before changing Notes detail IA, chips, panels, create flows, or in-detail shortcuts.

Scope boundary: **`docs/adr/019-notes-long-term-markdown-workspace.md`**. Notes is a workspace manager — not an in-app Markdown editor.

## Chips — do NOT

- Add an **Inbox** left chip (Inbox is right-panel only, with `Inbox(n)` badge).
- Make **Today** a persistent selected view (it is a quick action → open/create daily note).
- Embed **Recent** inside the Outline tree.

## Create — always

- Toolbar **+ Note** / **+ Folder** and `⌘N` / `⌘⇧N` in Tree mode.
- Default parent: selected folder → parent of note → Inbox → root.
- New notes open in Typora after create; context menu uses right-clicked row as parent.
- Launcher `n new` targets Inbox only.

## Tree / Map — always

- In-panel `[Tree | Map]` toggle; no modal mind-map sheet.
- Hide create buttons, filter, Expand/Collapse in Map mode.

## Scroll — always

- Call `syncOutlineDocumentFrame` / mind-map layout sync after expand, collapse, reload, resize.
- Partial expand must show scrollbar when content overflows.

## PR requirements

Update `NOTES_DETAIL_CONSTRAINTS.md`, `UX_BEHAVIOR_RULES.md`, `Features/Notes/README.md`, and `MANUAL_QA_CHECKLIST.md` when detail behavior changes.
